{"word":"H6253 - עַשְׁתֹּרֶת - ʻAshtôreth - ash-to'reth - Ashtoreth","slug":"H6253","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עַשְׁתֹּרֶת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻAshtôreth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ash-to'reth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Ashtoreth"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>עשׁתּרת</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>‛ashtôreth</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ash-to'reth</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Ashtoreth = \"star\" <ol><li>the principal female deity of the Phoenicians worshipped in war and fertility<ol type='a'><li>also 'Ishtar' of Assyria and 'Astarte' by the Greeks and Romans</li></ol></li></ol> <p />Origin: probably for <a href=\"#/H6251\">H6251</a> <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:1718 - 'ashtoret\">1718</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Feminine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1045\">H1045</a>, <a href=\"#/H6245\">H6245</a>, <a href=\"#/H6248\">H6248</a>, <a href=\"#/H6249\">H6249</a>, <a href=\"#/H6250\">H6250</a>, <a href=\"#/H6251\">H6251</a>, <a href=\"#/H6252\">H6252</a>, <a href=\"#/H6254\">H6254</a>, <a href=\"#/H6255\">H6255</a>"}]}